Dear Customer,
At the onset, we thank you for your continuous Patronage to Prakash Chemicals
International.
The objective of this communication is to update on Red Sea Challenges leading to
Force Majeure Situation with Shipping lines & therefore Logistics issues.
1. What it means for the shipments already sailed.
 Higher transit time
 Possibility of revision in freights
Reasons
 Most of the shipping lines have decided to avoid transit through Suez Canal
 Shipping Lines will reroute their vessels via Cape of Good Hope
2. What it means for the orders booked but not sailed.
 The freight needs to be revised in PFI and actual freights will be applicable ,
which we will be communicating to you.
 The freights is having daily changes so your immediate attention and
confirmation will be highly appreciated
 Alternatively, the order needs to be revised to FOB as per mutual agreement.
 The war Surcharge as communicated by shipping lines to the tune of $1500 +
per shipment will be levied to the each order. The amount varies daily
Reasons
 Shipping Lines have temporarily kept on hold any new Bookings to specific
regions & they may not be honoring even the old rate contracts to Europe
 All shipping lines will implement War Risk Surcharge with immediate effect.

3. What it means for the future orders.
 Freight will be dynamic and the freight will be communicated at the time of
booking.
 The freights is having daily changes so your immediate attention and
confirmation will be highly appreciated
 The war Surcharge as communicated by shipping lines to the tune of $1500 + (as
per communication from shipping line) per shipment will be levied to the each
order.
 The insurance cost may also go up for the consignments.
Reason
 There will be an Upward Freight revision on all the orders and future shipments
As normal business even if there is any hike in the freight charges in regular course
Prakash chemicals absorbs these charges. However force majeure and the war
situation is something beyond the anyone's control, and abnormal situations need to
some measures to mitigate the business risk.
We seek your support and cooperation for the same
Mr.Manish Shah
Managing Director
Prakash Chemicals International Pvt Ltd
